## SRS Acceptance Criteria → Phase Mapping

| Acceptance Criterion (SRS §9) | Phase |
|---|---|
| Build and publish surveys using categories from question bank | P2 + P3 |
| Campaign distributes via link/embed/email | P4 |
| Runtime enforces settings (CAPTCHA, limits, closures, restrictions) | P6 |
| Reports show completion and answer breakdown | P6 |
| Weighted scoring computed exactly per formula | P5 |
| Activation blocked when weights ≠ 100% | P5 |
| Admin configures external auth trust; validates test tokens | P7 |
| Respondents access surveys without SE login when external auth configured | P7 |
| Post-publish modification attempts rejected | P3 |
| Question/category edits after publish create new versions | P2 |
| Submitted responses locked unless admin reopen policy applied | P6 |

---

## Test Strategy

| Layer | Tool | Scope |
|---|---|---|
| Unit Tests | JUnit 5 + Mockito | Services, state machines, scoring engine, validators |
| Integration Tests | Spring Boot Test + Testcontainers (PostgreSQL, Redis, RabbitMQ) | Full REST API flows, DB persistence, lifecycle transitions |
| Coverage Gate | JaCoCo (already configured — 35% bundle, 40% service package) | Enforced via `./gradlew check` |
| Mutation Testing | PIT (already configured) | Service layer critical paths |

**Run all tests:** `./gradlew clean test`  
**Run with coverage verification:** `./gradlew clean check`

---

## Verification Plan

Each phase will be verified by:

1. **`./gradlew clean test`** — all unit + integration tests pass.
2. **`./gradlew clean check`** — JaCoCo coverage thresholds met.
3. **Manual API smoke test** — key endpoints exercised via `curl` or HTTP client against a running dev instance (`./gradlew bootRun`).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan covers **only** the scope defined in [survey-engine-mvp-srs.md](file:///home/amnayem/Projects/personal/Survey-Engine/docs/survey-engine-mvp-srs.md). Items listed in §2.2 (AI insights, BI pipelines, advanced multi-tenant perms) and §10 (future extensions) are explicitly excluded.
